const_crossmodule_inline — E2E cross-module const fixture (#594 crumb 8d)
===========================================================================

This directory is NOT a buildable project by itself (it has no top-level `.tkp`): it is
a PAIR of projects, discovered and driven ONLY by scripts/crossmodule_regressions.sh —
the generic examples/regressions/ build-all loops (sanitizers.yml, native.yml's
compile_fail_regressions.sh) glob a `.tkp` directly inside each fixture directory, so
they skip this one by construction and never see a dep that has not been provisioned.

Layout:
  dep/          a `kind = "package"` library (name "m1") exporting
                `pub const P: i64 = 20` and `exp const Q: i64 = 22`.
  consumer/     a `kind = "binary"` project declaring `[dependencies] m1 = "0.0.0"` and
                referencing `P`/`Q` by BARE name (phase-1 spelling): `exit(P + Q)`.
  EXPECT_EXIT   the expected process exit code of the built consumer binary (42).

Driver steps (scripts/crossmodule_regressions.sh), per compiler under test:
  1. build dep/ (kind=package) into a scratch dir -> `m1-0.0.0.tkl`.
  2. copy consumer/ into a scratch working copy; create its `packages/` dir there and
     copy the `.tkl` in (NEVER written into this committed tree — mktemp -d + a `trap`
     cleanup on exit, so the working tree and fixpoint/byte-identity stay unaffected).
  3. build the scratch consumer copy -> a binary; run it; assert its exit code equals
     EXPECT_EXIT (42).

Phase-2 (after #594 crumb 8c merges): the consumer flips to the qualified `m1::P`/`m1::Q`
spelling, proving the namespace-qualified value path end-to-end (still exit 42).
